<exercise>
<statement><p>
If a particle has constant mass <m>m</m>, position <m>\vr</m>, and is moving with velocity <m>\vv</m>, then its angular momentum is <m>\vL=m(\vr\times\vv)</m>.
</p>

<p>For a particle with mass <m>m=1</m> and position function <m>\vr=(\sin t, \cos t, t)</m>, find <m>\left|\diff{\vL}{t} \right|</m>.
